The proof in the previous problem does not work. But if we modify the "fact," we can get a working proof. Prove that [`\renewcommand{\v}{\vtx{above}{}}\newcommand{\lt}{<}n + 3 \lt n + 7`] for all values of [`\renewcommand{\d}{\displaystyle}\newcommand{\N}{\mathbb N}n \in \N\text{.}`] You can do this proof with algebra (without induction), but the goal of this exercise is to write out a valid induction proof.

